{"status":200,"currentLocale":"en","ranges":{"23020001-23020999":{"citation":"Isaiah&nbsp;20:1-6","link":"https:\/\/www.jw.org\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/isaiah\/20\/#v23020001-v23020006","validRange":"23020001-23020006","html":"<span class=\"verse\" id=\"v23020001\"><span class=\"style-b\"><span class=\"chapterNum\"><a href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#v23020001' data-anchor='#v23020001'>20 <\/a><\/span>\u00a0In the year that King Sar\u02b9gon of As\u00b7syr\u02b9i\u00b7a sent the Tar\u02b9tan<a class=\"footnoteLink\" id=\"footnotesource16336017\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#fn16336017' data-anchor='#fn16336017'>*<\/a> to Ash\u02b9dod,<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16335979\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16335979\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"6013002-6013003\">+<\/a> he fought against Ash\u02b9dod and captured it.<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16335993\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16335993\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"30001008\">+<\/a><\/span><\/span>\n\n<span class=\"verse\" id=\"v23020002\"><span class=\"style-b\"><sup class=\"verseNum\"><a href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#v23020002' data-anchor='#v23020002'>2\u00a0<\/a><\/sup>\u00a0At that time Jehovah spoke through Isaiah<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16336040\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16336040\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"23001001\">+<\/a> the son of A\u02b9moz, saying: \u201cGo, remove the sackcloth from your hips, and take your sandals off your feet.\u201d And he did so, walking about naked<a class=\"footnoteLink\" id=\"footnotesource16336055\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#fn16336055' data-anchor='#fn16336055'>*<\/a> and barefoot.<\/span>\n<span class=\"parabreak\"><\/span><\/span>\n\n<span class=\"verse\" id=\"v23020003\"><span class=\"style-b first\"><sup class=\"verseNum\"><a href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#v23020003' data-anchor='#v23020003'>3\u00a0<\/a><\/sup>\u00a0Jehovah then said: \u201cJust as my servant Isaiah has walked about naked and barefoot for three years as a sign<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16336082\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16336082\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"23008018\">+<\/a> and a portent against Egypt<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16336102\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16336102\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"23019001\">+<\/a> and E\u00b7thi\u00b7o\u02b9pi\u00b7a,<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16336116\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16336116\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"23018001\">+<\/a><\/span><\/span>\n\n<span class=\"verse\" id=\"v23020004\"><span class=\"style-b\"><sup class=\"verseNum\"><a href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#v23020004' data-anchor='#v23020004'>4\u00a0<\/a><\/sup>\u00a0so the king of As\u00b7syr\u02b9i\u00b7a will lead the captives of Egypt<a class=\"xrefLink jsBibleLink\" id=\"xreflink16336146\" href=\"\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/mcr\/16336146\/\" data-bible=\"nwt\" data-targetverses=\"23019004\">+<\/a> and the exiles of E\u00b7thi\u00b7o\u02b9pi\u00b7a, boys and old men, naked and barefoot and with exposed buttocks, the nakedness<a class=\"footnoteLink\" id=\"footnotesource16336160\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#fn16336160' data-anchor='#fn16336160'>*<\/a> of Egypt.<\/span><\/span>\n\n<span class=\"verse\" id=\"v23020005\"><span class=\"style-b\"><sup class=\"verseNum\"><a href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#v23020005' data-anchor='#v23020005'>5\u00a0<\/a><\/sup>\u00a0And they will be terrified and will be ashamed of E\u00b7thi\u00b7o\u02b9pi\u00b7a their hope and of Egypt their pride.<a class=\"footnoteLink\" id=\"footnotesource16336189\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#fn16336189' data-anchor='#fn16336189'>*<\/a><\/span><\/span>\n\n<span class=\"verse\" id=\"v23020006\"><span class=\"style-b\"><sup class=\"verseNum\"><a href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#v23020006' data-anchor='#v23020006'>6\u00a0<\/a><\/sup>\u00a0The inhabitants of this coastland will say in that day, \u2018Look at what happened to our hope, to which we fled for help and rescue from the king of As\u00b7syr\u02b9i\u00b7a! How will we escape now?\u2019\u201d<\/span><span class=\"parabreak\"><\/span><\/span>\n\n","footnotes":"<div class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn16336017\"><a class=\"fnSourceLink\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#footnotesource16336017' data-anchor='#footnotesource16336017'>^&nbsp;<\/a><span class=\"\">Or \u201cthe commander.\u201d<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn16336055\"><a class=\"fnSourceLink\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#footnotesource16336055' data-anchor='#footnotesource16336055'>^&nbsp;<\/a><span class=\"\">Or \u201clightly clad.\u201d<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn16336160\"><a class=\"fnSourceLink\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#footnotesource16336160' data-anchor='#footnotesource16336160'>^&nbsp;<\/a><span class=\"\">Or \u201cto the shame.\u201d<\/span><\/div>\n\n<div class=\"footnote\" id=\"fn16336189\"><a class=\"fnSourceLink\" href='\/en\/publications\/bible\/nwt\/books\/json\/html\/23020001-23020999#footnotesource16336189' data-anchor='#footnotesource16336189'>^&nbsp;<\/a><span class=\"\">Or \u201cwhose beauty they admired.\u201d<\/span><\/div>\n\n"}}}